flavor_text: It spins string not only from its rear but also fromits mouth. It is hard to tell which end is which.
A single strand of a special string is endlessly spunout of its rear. The string leads back to its nest.
Rather than mak ing a nest in one specific spot itwanders in search of food after darkness falls.
ARIADOS's feet are tipped with tiny hooked claws that enable it to scuttle on ceilings and vertical walls.This Pokemon constricts the foe with thin and strong silk webbing.
